<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-27T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-27T11:00:00-05:00" n="465" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">760c.61/259: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-27T18:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">August
                                            27, 1920—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 29—2
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>468. Consul at Danzig telegraphs 25th that as a result of energetic
                                measures taken by Great Britain and France ammunition for Poland is
                                now being forwarded to its destination by the Free City. Naval
                                forces have been reinforced and everything quiet. Some of ammunition
                                being unloaded by Danzig laborers.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>